            "mimeType": "application/json",
            "size": 2105,
            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\"id\":\"msg_015zRrpeGNaTgwVQ7c4vKjD9\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Great question! Let me explain how Google Ads pairs your headlines and descriptions together:\\n\\n**How They Work Together:**\\n\\nGoogle Ads uses a **dynamic pairing system** where it automatically combines your headlines and descriptions in different ways to find the best-performing combinations. Here's what happens:\\n\\n1. **Multiple Combinations**: Google will test different pairings of your headlines with your descriptions. For example:\\n   - Headline 1 + Description 1\\n   - Headline 2 + Description 2\\n   - Headline 3 + Description 1\\n   - And so on...\\n\\n2. **Display Format**: When your ad shows, Google displays:\\n   - **Up to 3 headlines** (stacked vertically at the top)\\n   - **Up to 2 descriptions** (below the headlines)\\n\\n3. **Optimization**: Google's algorithm learns which combinations get the most clicks and conversions, then automatically shows the best-performing pairings more often.\\n\\n**Why This Matters for Your Scheduling Tool:**\\n\\nYour headlines should work **independently** (each one should make sense on its own) AND **together** (they should complement each other when shown as a group). Your descriptions should then expand on the value proposition and provide the next logical step.\\n\\nFor example:\\n- **Headlines** might emphasize the problem (\\\"Tired of Scheduling Chaos?\\\") and the solution (\\\"Find Meeting Times Instantly\\\")\\n- **Descriptions** could then provide proof (\\\"Used by 2,000+ teams\\\") and a call-to-action (\\\"Get your free trial today\\\")\\n\\nThis way, no matter which combination Google tests, your message stays cohesive and compelling!\\n\\nWould you like me to generate your headlines and descriptions now, keeping this pairing strategy in mind?\"}],\"stop_reason\":\"end_turn\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":2316,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":0},\"output_tokens\":387,\"service_tier\":\"standard\"}}"
          },
