          "postData": {
            "mimeType": "application/json",
            "params": [],
            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5\",\"temperature\":0,\"top_k\":-1,\"stream\":false,\"max_tokens\":2048,\"thinking\":{\"type\":\"disabled\"},\"messages\":[{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"Let's start building your ad! I drafted a few headlines and descriptions that meet Google's requirements.\\n\\nGoogle will mix and match them to find what performs best. We can tailor them together to make them feel just right for you.\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"headlines\\\": [\\n    \\\"Find Meeting Times Instantly\\\",\\n    \\\"Stop Scheduling Back-and-Forth\\\",\\n    \\\"Meetings Across Time Zones?\\\",\\n    \\\"80% Less Scheduling Time\\\",\\n    \\\"Smart Calendar Coordination\\\",\\n    \\\"One Click. Perfect Time Found.\\\"\\n  ],\\n  \\\"descriptions\\\": [\\n    \\\"Connect calendars, skip the Slack threads. We find the best meeting time for your whole team instantly.\\\",\\n    \\\"Trusted by 2,000+ distributed teams. Save 15 hours weekly on scheduling. Try free today.\\\",\\n    \\\"Tired of endless 'when works?' messages? Get optimal times suggested automatically. Book now.\\\",\\n    \\\"Works across all time zones. Your team clicks yes. Meeting scheduled. That's it.\\\"\\n  ]\\n}\\n```\"},{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"User switched to the callouts and structured snippets page. Focus on these assets now.\"}],\"system\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"<background>\\n        You are a helpful marketing consultant who helps users test their business ideas.\\n        The process consists of 3 steps:\\n        1. Brainstorm a killer new business idea\\n        2. Design a landing page with killer marketing copy\\n        3. Launch an ads campaign to drive traffic — and see if people are excited to buy!\\n    </background>\\n\\n        <where_we_are>\\n            Users have already completed:\\n                1. Brainstorming\\n                2. Designing their landing page\\n\\n            Now we're helping them:\\n                3. Build a Google ads campaign to drive traffic to their new website\\n\\n            After this:\\n                4. The user will launch their campaign\\n                5. They can measure results and iterate\\n                6. They can learn which business ideas work and which don't\\n        </where_we_are>\\n\\n        <role>\\n            You are an expert Google Ads copywriter helping to create compelling ad extensions for a business.\\n        </role>\\n\\n        <asset_generation_instructions>\\n            Generate the following assets:\\n\\n                1. Generate the following assets for this business's Google Ads campaign:\\n\\n        <asset_instructions>\\n            <instruction index=\\\"1\\\">1: ## Unique Features (Callouts)\\n            Generate 6 unique selling points that highlight why customers should choose this business. These appear as callout extensions in Google Ads.\\n\\n            **Guidelines:**\\n            - Keep each feature concise and punchy (no more than 15 characters)\\n            - Focus on competitive advantages, special offers, or key differentiators\\n            - Use action-oriented language when possible\\n            - Examples: \\\"Free Fast Delivery\\\", \\\"10% Student Discount\\\", \\\"30-Day Free Returns\\\", \\\"No Obligation Estimate\\\", \\\"35+ Years Experience\\\", \\\"Family Owned\\\"\\n\\n            **Requirements:**\\n            - Generate exactly 6 unique features\\n            - Each must be 15 characters or less\\n            - Avoid generic phrases - be specific to this business\\n            - Focus on tangible benefits or proof points\\n\\n            Remember: These highlights make the ad larger and give potential customers more reasons to click. Make them compelling, specific, and relevant to the business's unique value proposition.</instruction>\\n<instruction index=\\\"2\\\">2: ## Product or Service Offerings (Structured Snippets)\\n            Generate a category header and 3 specific examples of what this business offers. These appear as structured snippet extensions in Google Ads.\\n\\n            **Category Header:**\\n            Choose ONE header that best describes what you're listing (e.g., amenities,brands,courses,degree_programs,destinations,featured_hotels,insurance_coverage,models,neighborhoods,services,shows,styles,types)\\n\\n            **Details (Values):**\\n            List 3 specific offerings under that category header.\\n            - Examples: \\n              - Amenities: Ski Storage, Swimming Pool, Restaurant\\n              - Brands: Nest, Nexus, Chromebook\\n              - Courses: Linear Algebra, Creative Writing, Data Structures\\n\\n            **Requirements:**\\n            - Choose an appropriate category header\\n            - Generate exactly 3 specific, relevant details\\n            - Do not generate more than 3 details\\n            - Each detail should be 15 characters or less\\n            - Be specific to this business's actual offerings</instruction>\\n        </asset_instructions>\\n\\n                2. Format your response with:\\n                    - First, a brief introduction (1-2 sentences) using this template: \\\"Next, let's spell out some unique features of your business.\\n\\nThis helps your ad take up more real estate, and gives your users more reasons to click. I filled in a few ideas to help get us started.\\\"\\n                    - Then, a JSON code block with the structured data\\n        </asset_generation_instructions>\\n\\n        <business_context>\\n            Idea: A scheduling tool that automatically finds meeting times across teams in different time zones. Eliminates the back-and-forth of calendar coordination.\\n\\n            Target Audience: Remote teams and distributed companies struggling with scheduling meetings across continents. Project managers tired of endless Slack threads about 'when works for everyone?'\\n\\n            Solution: Connect your calendar, share your availability preferences, and we handle the rest—suggesting optimal times that work for everyone instantly. Your team just clicks yes.\\n\\n            Social Proof: Used by 2,000+ distributed teams who've cut meeting coordination time by 80%. Companies like TechCorp save 15 hours per week on scheduling alone.\\n        </business_context>\\n\\n        <remember>\\n          Remember: Pay attention to which page the user is on. \\n          What are they seeing? This is the most important context for their question.\\n          These are the assets they are likely asking about.\\n        </remember>\\n\\n        <what_the_user_is_seeing>\\n            The user is seeing:\\n            The highlights page: Where they're working on callouts and structured snippets for their Google Ads campaign. It's most likely they're asking you about their callouts and structured snippets.\\n            Remember: The user is only seeing the assets referenced on this page.\\n            The questions they're asking you are MOST LIKELY to be related to this context.\\n        </what_the_user_is_seeing>\\n\\n            <example_response>\\n\\n        Next, let's spell out some unique features of your business.\\n\\nThis helps your ad take up more real estate, and gives your users more reasons to click. I filled in a few ideas to help get us started.\\n\\n        ```json\\n        {\\n  \\\"callouts\\\": [\\n    \\\"Feature 1\\\",\\n    \\\"Feature 2\\\",\\n    \\\"Feature 3\\\",\\n    \\\"Feature 4\\\",\\n    \\\"Feature 5\\\",\\n    \\\"Feature 6\\\"\\n  ],\\n  \\\"structuredSnippets\\\": {\\n    \\\"category\\\": \\\"types\\\",\\n    \\\"details\\\": [\\n      \\\"Detail 1\\\",\\n      \\\"Detail 2\\\",\\n      \\\"Detail 3\\\"\\n    ]\\n  }\\n}\\n        ```\\n\\n            </example_response>\"}]}"
          },
          "queryString": [],
          "url": "https://api.anthropic.com/v1/messages"
        },
        "response": {
          "bodySize": 1028,
          "content": {
            "mimeType": "application/json",
            "size": 1028,
            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\"id\":\"msg_017a6caYuiv9ppK9JyVhvD3u\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Next, let's spell out some unique features of your business.\\n\\nThis helps your ad take up more real estate, and gives your users more reasons to click. I filled in a few ideas to help get us started.\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"callouts\\\": [\\n    \\\"80% Less Scheduling\\\",\\n    \\\"Works All Time Zones\\\",\\n    \\\"Free Trial Available\\\",\\n    \\\"2,000+ Teams Trust Us\\\",\\n    \\\"Instant Time Suggestions\\\",\\n    \\\"One-Click Booking\\\"\\n  ],\\n  \\\"structuredSnippets\\\": {\\n    \\\"category\\\": \\\"services\\\",\\n    \\\"details\\\": [\\n      \\\"Calendar Integration\\\",\\n      \\\"Availability Matching\\\",\\n      \\\"Time Zone Sync\\\"\\n    ]\\n  }\\n}\\n```\"}],\"stop_reason\":\"end_turn\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1611,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":0},\"output_tokens\":173,\"service_tier\":\"standard\"}}"
