            "size": 1730,
            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\"id\":\"msg_01RLfm5YkojcV8Esh73TTkJx\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Great question! **Descriptions** are the supporting text lines that appear below your headlines in Google Ads.\\n\\nHere's what you need to know about them:\\n\\n**Key Details:**\\n- **Length limit:** Up to 70 characters each (strict Google limit)\\n- **Placement:** They appear below your headlines in search results\\n- **How many show:** Google typically displays up to 2 description lines in a single ad\\n- **Purpose:** They give you space to explain benefits, features, and calls to action\\n\\n**What they do:**\\nDescriptions expand on the promise made in your headlines. While headlines grab attention, descriptions convince people to click by providing more detail about your offer, social proof, or a specific call-to-action.\\n\\n**For your scheduling tool**, descriptions would highlight things like:\\n- How much time teams save (e.g., \\\"Cut meeting coordination by 80%\\\")\\n- Key benefits (e.g., \\\"Works across all time zones instantly\\\")\\n- Social proof (e.g., \\\"Trusted by 2,000+ distributed teams\\\")\\n- Clear calls-to-action (e.g., \\\"Get your free trial today\\\")\\n\\nSince Google mixes and matches your descriptions with your headlines, you want them to work together to tell a compelling story about why someone should click your ad.\\n\\nWould you like me to generate some descriptions for your scheduling tool campaign?\"}],\"stop_reason\":\"end_turn\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":2587,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":0},\"output_tokens\":300,\"service_tier\":\"standard\"}}"
